1
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:44,280
Ghost

2
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:45,159
Soldier

3
00:00:45,799 --> 00:00:46,039
Battle

4
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:46,880
Fighter

5
00:00:47,119 --> 00:00:47,439
Brother

6
00:00:47,439 --> 00:00:48,119
Ghost

7
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:50,280
Brother

8
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:51,399
With so little courage,

9
00:00:51,399 --> 00:00:52,280
you dare take on jobs?

10
00:00:53,799 --> 00:00:54,640
Xiao Lian.

11
00:01:01,079 --> 00:01:02,000
What are you doing here?

12
00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:04,840
I followed you the whole way.

13
00:01:06,599 --> 00:01:07,439
You haven't even finished training,

14
00:01:07,439 --> 00:01:08,439
and you're already taking jobs?

15
00:01:08,439 --> 00:01:09,680
Aren't you scared Master will find out

16
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:10,480
and skin you alive?

17
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:11,599
I'm just trying to earn

18
00:01:11,599 --> 00:01:12,599
some money for the family.

19
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:14,560
Didn't you hear Aunt Xiao Ling?

20
00:01:15,439 --> 00:01:15,959
Our Bone-Keeping Temple

21
00:01:15,959 --> 00:01:17,040
has no income anymore.

22
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:20,120
At least Master didn't spoil you for nothing.

23
00:01:21,599 --> 00:01:23,040
Master spoils you, not me.

24
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:30,599
Let me do it.

25
00:01:35,439 --> 00:01:36,719
Cleanse the ears with light, hear all directions.

26
00:01:36,719 --> 00:01:37,719
Sounds clear and sharp.

27
00:01:38,239 --> 00:01:38,799
Cleanse the mouth with light,

28
00:01:38,799 --> 00:01:39,400
eat beef and mutton,

29
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:40,359
taste fresh and delicious.

30
00:01:40,920 --> 00:01:41,959
Cleanse the chest with light, bright and clear,

31
00:01:41,959 --> 00:01:42,959
heart open and honest.

32
00:01:43,319 --> 00:01:43,799
Cleanse the hands with light,

33
00:01:43,799 --> 00:01:45,280
gather wealth and grain, plentiful in all.

34
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:46,200
Cleanse the feet with light,

35
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:48,079
rise to heaven, soul at rest.

36
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,680
Not bad, little sister.

37
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:52,599
You're just too dumb.

38
00:01:52,719 --> 00:01:53,719
Master's done it hundreds of times,

39
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:54,519
yet you're the only one who can't learn it.

40
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:00,920
And this is...?

41
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:02,680
This is my sister, Xiao Lian.

42
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:03,959
She's helping me with the funeral.

43
00:02:05,599 --> 00:02:06,599
Thank you both for your trouble.

44
00:02:08,439 --> 00:02:09,120
Brother-in-law,

45
00:02:09,719 --> 00:02:10,560
please make yourself at home.

46
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,400
Brother...

47
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:15,919
how could you just die like this?

48
00:02:17,879 --> 00:02:19,840
Father has already agreed

49
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,879
to your marriage.

50
00:02:23,319 --> 00:02:24,479
It's my fault.

51
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:29,000
My fault for being one step too late.

52
00:02:29,759 --> 00:02:30,520
Brother-in-law,

53
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,479
please accept my condolences.

54
00:02:38,719 --> 00:02:39,560
Sister-in-law,

55
00:02:40,479 --> 00:02:41,639
a word in private.

56
00:02:41,879 --> 00:02:42,439
Father

57
00:02:42,919 --> 00:02:44,199
has some matters to convey.

58
00:02:56,879 --> 00:02:57,879
How did he die?

59
00:02:58,199 --> 00:02:59,360
The family said he drowned.

60
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:00,639
Drowned?

61
00:03:00,879 --> 00:03:01,319
What's wrong?

62
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:05,800
Something's off.

63
00:03:06,639 --> 00:03:07,400
What's so strange about it?

64
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:09,800
I can't quite explain

65
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:10,759
what feels off about it.

66
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:11,840
But it's not like the other

67
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:12,759
drowning cases I've seen.

68
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:14,319
What's so strange about that?

69
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:15,879
Some drown in rivers,

70
00:03:15,879 --> 00:03:16,719
some drown in lakes,

71
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:18,240
some even drown in a washbasin.

72
00:03:22,479 --> 00:03:22,879
Oh no.

73
00:03:22,879 --> 00:03:23,479
Now what?

74
00:03:23,479 --> 00:03:24,439
Quit freaking out.

75
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:26,319
Master said a cat can't cross a coffin.

76
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,039
The corpse will rise.

77
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:28,319
Watch me.

78
00:03:31,919 --> 00:03:32,280
Shoo!

79
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,360
You know what,

80
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,240
this is actually pretty good.

81
00:03:38,639 --> 00:03:39,240
What are you doing?

82
00:03:41,759 --> 00:03:42,439
The family didn't bother to

83
00:03:42,439 --> 00:03:43,240
prepare any food for us.

84
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,039
I'm starving.

85
00:03:47,879 --> 00:03:48,919
Master said,

86
00:03:48,919 --> 00:03:50,360
"Starve before eating grave offerings."

87
00:03:51,319 --> 00:03:52,159
Well, I'm eating it.

88
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:52,960
What's the worst that could happen?

89
00:03:53,319 --> 00:03:54,039
I just don't believe

90
00:03:54,039 --> 00:03:55,080
he'll jump out and bite me.

91
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,879
Not only am I eating,

92
00:03:57,159 --> 00:03:57,919
I'm gonna drink too.

93
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:01,719
What is this stuff?

94
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,520
Why does Master love this so much?

95
00:04:04,159 --> 00:04:04,719
You're really

96
00:04:04,719 --> 00:04:06,280
going too far these days.

97
00:04:08,039 --> 00:04:08,439
What?

98
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,360
Got a problem with that?

99
00:04:12,599 --> 00:04:14,159
Master nags me every day.

100
00:04:14,599 --> 00:04:16,199
I finally get a couple of peaceful days,

101
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:17,920
and now you're on my case too?

102
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:18,480
Brother, what's wrong?

103
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:19,120
Brother!

104
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:19,879
Brother!

105
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:25,120
Xiao Lian!

106
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:26,120
Are you okay?

107
00:04:28,519 --> 00:04:29,079
What happened?

108
00:04:29,399 --> 00:04:30,519
My brother ate the offerings,

109
00:04:30,519 --> 00:04:31,240
and then this happened.

110
00:04:31,839 --> 00:04:32,399
Dongsheng!

111
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:33,399
Dongsheng!

112
00:04:44,319 --> 00:04:44,680
This...

113
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:45,800
What's going on here?

114
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,160
Quick!

115
00:04:53,439 --> 00:04:54,319
Have him take this.

116
00:04:56,959 --> 00:04:58,079
How is the deceased related to you?

117
00:04:58,879 --> 00:04:59,720
He's my brother.

118
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:05,600
How did he die?

119
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,680
He drowned, didn't he?

120
00:05:15,639 --> 00:05:17,519
Brother!

121
00:05:17,759 --> 00:05:19,279
I've failed you.

122
00:05:19,639 --> 00:05:20,800
Even after your death,

123
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,680
your body has been desecrated.

124
00:05:23,519 --> 00:05:25,079
You disrespected my brother.

125
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,199
I'm reporting this to the authorities.

126
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:30,839
Aren't you going to stop me?

127
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,439
Aren't you going?

128
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:34,639
Forget...

129
00:05:34,639 --> 00:05:35,000
Forget it.

130
00:05:35,399 --> 00:05:36,279
I'll be the bigger person.

131
00:05:36,399 --> 00:05:36,879
You...

132
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:37,519
Just go, go on.

133
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,120
I'll find someone else.

134
00:05:39,639 --> 00:05:40,240
You can't just leave.

135
00:05:41,639 --> 00:05:42,360
I'm from Yinyang Du,

136
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,639
the Lamp Keeper of Bone-Keeping Temple.

137
00:05:43,959 --> 00:05:44,639
Other than me,

138
00:05:44,639 --> 00:05:45,759
you won't find anyone better.

139
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,680
Normally,

140
00:05:47,759 --> 00:05:49,399
we only handle where the dead go,

141
00:05:49,639 --> 00:05:50,480
not where they came from.

142
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:53,079
But today, you hurt my apprentice.

143
00:05:54,439 --> 00:05:55,959
You said your brother drowned, right?

144
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,199
But when I struck him,

145
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,279
he should've spat out water,

146
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,079
not black blood.

147
00:06:03,519 --> 00:06:04,839
He spat out black blood,

148
00:06:05,759 --> 00:06:07,079
which means he was poisoned.

149
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:08,680
And one more thing.

150
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:09,759
Some people are pretty stupid.

151
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:11,800
After committing the crime,

152
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,839
they don't even destroy the murder weapon,

153
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:17,079
which is why my apprentice got hurt.

154
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:18,399
You scared me to death.

155
00:06:20,959 --> 00:06:22,639
These are all just assumptions,

156
00:06:25,319 --> 00:06:25,839
right?

157
00:06:26,319 --> 00:06:27,439
Even if my brother was...

158
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:27,920
poisoned...

159
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,639
poisoned to death,

160
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,319
what if my brother gave up on life

161
00:06:30,439 --> 00:06:31,360
and drank the poisoned wine himself?

162
00:06:31,519 --> 00:06:31,879
Right?

163
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,519
Fair point.

164
00:06:37,839 --> 00:06:38,920
Then why did you say

165
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:39,920
he drowned?

166
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:41,120
I...

167
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,040
I just got here, didn't I?

168
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:42,279
I...

169
00:06:42,879 --> 00:06:44,480
I just heard it from someone else.

170
00:06:45,519 --> 00:06:46,040
It was him.

171
00:06:46,759 --> 00:06:47,920
It was all his idea.

172
00:06:48,839 --> 00:06:50,800
A few days after my husband and I married,

173
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,279
he forced himself on me.

174
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,680
I couldn't bear the torment,

175
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:57,920
so my husband and I moved here.

176
00:06:59,399 --> 00:07:00,120
Unexpectedly,

177
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:01,879
he found us again,

178
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:02,879
and forced me

179
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,160
to murder

180
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,560
my own husband.

181
00:07:06,959 --> 00:07:07,879
With your family's mess,

182
00:07:08,079 --> 00:07:08,920
don't come to me again.

183
00:07:09,279 --> 00:07:09,920
I'm done with this.

184
00:07:10,199 --> 00:07:11,079
I'm done with this for good.

185
00:07:11,279 --> 00:07:12,079
I'm just not getting involved.

186
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:27,639
Let's go.

187
00:07:38,399 --> 00:07:39,040
Ruling.

188
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:41,519
Go report this to the local constable later.

189
00:08:04,439 --> 00:08:05,160
Forget it.

190
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,920
This might be the best ending for her.

191
00:08:09,959 --> 00:08:10,439
Let's go.

192
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:36,440
Brother.

193
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,159
You're awake.

194
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:41,600
Master.

195
00:08:42,639 --> 00:08:44,120
This is the money I earned for you.

196
00:08:47,559 --> 00:08:48,360
You went there just

197
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,519
to earn me this little bit of money?

198
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:50,759
It's the kid's good intention.

199
00:08:50,919 --> 00:08:51,720
What are you doing?

200
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,919
He's going to be a Lamp Keeper one day.

201
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,200
Do I need him to earn this petty cash?

202
00:08:58,039 --> 00:08:59,039
The dead deserve the utmost respect.

203
00:08:59,279 --> 00:09:00,759
How could you mess around like that?

204
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:19,759
Brother.

205
00:09:21,039 --> 00:09:22,399
Are you feeling better?

206
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:24,120
Just go.

207
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:26,200
I want to sleep for a bit.

208
00:09:43,519 --> 00:09:45,279
Is Dongsheng feeling better?

209
00:09:45,639 --> 00:09:47,120
He just took his medicine, much better.

210
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:48,399
Look at you now,

211
00:09:48,399 --> 00:09:49,320
suddenly caring about him.

212
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,000
Weren't you the one

213
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:50,759
scolding him this morning?

214
00:09:51,639 --> 00:09:52,720
He's going to be

215
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,639
a Lamp Keeper someday.

216
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:54,679
Of course I have to be

217
00:09:54,679 --> 00:09:55,679
strict with him, right?

218
00:09:55,879 --> 00:09:57,120
Did you ever ask the boy what he wants?

219
00:09:57,399 --> 00:09:58,759
You think anyone wants to be like you,

220
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,600
stuck in this Bone-Keeping Temple for life?

221
00:10:00,879 --> 00:10:01,679
What's that supposed to mean?

222
00:10:02,399 --> 00:10:03,320
Someone's got to do

223
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,240
this job, right?

224
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,480
What do I mean?

225
00:10:05,519 --> 00:10:06,320
It's the Republic era now.

226
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,320
Times are changing.

227
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,600
So what if times are changing?

228
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,039
People still die, don't they?

229
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,080
As long as people die,

230
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:15,279
someone has to guard the graves.

231
00:10:15,919 --> 00:10:16,519
Am I right?

232
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,399
Typical woman's view.

233
00:10:21,919 --> 00:10:22,720
Drink, drink, drink.

234
00:10:22,879 --> 00:10:23,440
That's for drinking too much!

235
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:26,840
Pick it up for me.

236
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:27,320
I won't.

237
00:10:27,559 --> 00:10:27,960
Pick it up!

238
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:28,600
No.

239
00:10:31,639 --> 00:10:32,600
Fine, I'll pick it up myself.

240
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:37,360
Don't be angry.

241
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,039
Alright.

242
00:10:38,279 --> 00:10:39,639
Let's just talk things out, okay?

243
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:40,679
Oh, right.

244
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,279
There's another thing.

245
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,559
It's about Xiao Lian.

246
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,720
She's grown up now,

247
00:10:45,919 --> 00:10:47,120
a young woman.

248
00:10:47,799 --> 00:10:48,679
What are you getting at?

249
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,399
I don't mean anything.

250
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:51,600
I...

251
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,200
You...

252
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,159
What are you thinking?

253
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,200
I mean, don't let Xiao Lian

254
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,120
fool around with Dongsheng.

255
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:58,799
I heard

256
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:00,120
there's a school in the provincial capital

257
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:03,440
that trains physicians.

258
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:04,879
They're called doctors now,

259
00:11:05,159 --> 00:11:05,960
not "physicians."

260
00:11:06,639 --> 00:11:07,759
Fancy foreign terms, huh?

261
00:11:07,919 --> 00:11:08,679
Who are you cursing?

262
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,159
I'm trying to make a point!

263
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:11,879
What I'm saying is,

264
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,720
maybe we could send Xiao Lian

265
00:11:13,879 --> 00:11:14,559
over there.

266
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:17,759
I heard there's an entrance exam.

267
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:21,440
So you already knew about this?

268
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,200
Don't be like that.

269
00:11:26,639 --> 00:11:27,360
An exam?

270
00:11:27,399 --> 00:11:27,960
No problem.

271
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,840
My apprentice won't be afraid of any exam.

272
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:32,879
Then tonight I'll

273
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:34,200
talk to Xiao Lian about it.

274
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,919
Thank you, thank you.

275
00:11:39,519 --> 00:11:39,840
And, uh,

276
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,039
about Dongsheng's medicine,

277
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,320
remember to brew it for him.

278
00:11:52,639 --> 00:11:53,440
I'm not going.

279
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,240
I want to stay

280
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,320
by your side and Master's.

281
00:11:56,879 --> 00:11:58,679
Why are you so stubborn, girl?

282
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,519
This is what your Master wants.

283
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,399
I'm not going, no matter what.

284
00:12:03,759 --> 00:12:04,840
If anyone goes, let my brother go.

285
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:06,200
He's a boy.

286
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,399
What about boys?

287
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:11,559
Boys are meant to go far in the world.

288
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:12,960
I believe

289
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,600
my brother will become

290
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,360
just like Master,

291
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,759
a true, upstanding man.

292
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:18,919
Whether he goes far or not,

293
